  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Major abdominal surgeries are associated with perioperative cardiac morbidity of up to 10%.

      Ischemic preconditioning may have a protective effect. The purpose of this study is to find
      out remote ischemic conditioning by inflating a blood pressure cuff on the arm will have a
      protective effect.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
